  • Constructor Details

    • SQLDatabase

      public SQLDatabase​(DbConn db, int type) throws DatabaseDifferenceCheckerException
      Uses a database connection to initialize a HashMap of tables and views that exist in the database provided. Note: It will also SQL statements to drop all Primary Keys and remove all auot_increments in the database provided which will only be used on the live database
      Parameters:
      db - The database connection used to get the database information
      type - The type of datbase implimentation which is being used. Note: this allows for the appropriate turning off of Foreign Keys
      Throws:
      DatabaseDifferenceCheckerException - Error connecting or closing the database connection.

      This is the default constructor for this class, Needed for Serialization.

  • Method Details

    • getFirstSteps

      public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> getFirstSteps()
      Returns the first steps to be taken in order to run the SQL statements. These SQL statements are used to drop Primary Keys and remove auto_increments on the database provided. Note: this function will return an empty ArrayList if the function is called for the development database
      Returns:
      The first steps to be taken in order to run the SQL statements.

    • updateViews

      public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> updateViews​(java.util.ArrayList<View> liveViews)
      Takes in a list of views and returns the SQL statements needed to make the two databases have the exact same views. Note: all views in the live database will be dropped and all from the dev database will be created
      Parameters:
      liveViews - All of the views in the live database.
      Returns:
      The SQL statements to run in order to make the live database have the same views as the dev one.

    • compareTables

      public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> compareTables​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​Table> liveTables)
      Determines which tables are to be created and which are to be dropped.
      Parameters:
      liveTables - All tables in the live database where the key is the name of the table.
      Returns:
      The SQL statements to run in order to remove and/or create tables in the live database.

    • updateTables

      public java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> updateTables​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​Table> live, java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> updateTables)
      Takes in two table lists and returns the SQL statements to run in order to make the live database have the same table definitions as the dev one.
      Parameters:
      live - All tables in the live database where the key is the name of the table.
      updateTables - All the tables which are not the same in the live and development databases.
      Returns:

    • tablesDiffs

      public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> tablesDiffs​(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,​Table> liveTables, SQLDatabase liveDatabase)
      Compares the tables in the live and dev databases, and returns a list of table names whose structure did not match between the development and live databases.
      Parameters:
      liveTables - All tables in the live database where the key is the name of the table.
      liveDatabase - The live database connection which allows the live exclusions to be updated here to prevent unnecessary Primary Key dropping.
      Returns:
      The tables that are to be updated because their structures did not match between the development and live databases.
